      <h2>What This Means</h2>
      <p>Some of the links on Solopreneur Tools are affiliate links. This means that if you click on a link and make a purchase, I may receive a small commission at no extra cost to you.</p>

      <h2>Why I Use Affiliate Links</h2>
      <p>Running a website takes time, effort, and money. Affiliate commissions help cover:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Website hosting and domain costs</li>
        <li>Research time for testing and reviewing tools</li>
        <li>Content creation and maintenance</li>
        <li>Email and marketing tools</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>My Promise to You</h2>
      <p>I only recommend products and services that:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>I have personally used or thoroughly researched</li>
        <li>I believe will provide genuine value to solopreneurs</li>
        <li>I would recommend even without an affiliate relationship</li>
      </ul>

      <p>My reviews are based on honest assessments of each tool's features, pricing, and value. An affiliate relationship never influences my opinion or rating of a product.</p>

      <h2>Types of Affiliate Relationships</h2>
      <p>This site participates in affiliate programs including but not limited to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Amazon Associates</li>
        <li>Individual company affiliate programs</li>
        <li>Third-party affiliate networks</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Transparency</h2>
      <p>When a post contains affiliate links, I will clearly indicate this within the content or at the end of the article. This allows you to make informed decisions about your purchases.</p>

      <h2>Questions?</h2>
      <p>If you have any questions about my affiliate relationships or the products I recommend, please <a href="/contact">contact me</a>.</p>

      <h2>Your Support Matters</h2>
      <p>When you use my affiliate links, you're supporting independent content creation and helping me continue to provide free, valuable resources for solopreneurs. Thank you for your support!</p>
